<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 2479/95 of 25 October 1995 adapting to technical progress Council Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85 on recording equipment in road transport </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2479/95, millega kohandatakse tehnika arenguga n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 maanteevedudel kasutatavate s&otilde;idumeerikute kohta 25. oktoober 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> (Text with EEA relevance) </inglise>
<eesti> (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85 of 20 December 1985 on recording equipment in road transport (1), as last amended by the Act of Accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden, and in particular Article 17 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 20. detsembri 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 maanteevedudel kasutatavate s&otilde;idumeerikute kohta, (1) viimati muudetud Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisaktiga, eriti selle artiklit 17, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to eliminate the possibilities of fraud in the use of the electronic recording equipment in road transport; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja k&otilde;rvaldada pettusev&otilde;imalused maanteevedudel kasutatavate elektrooniliste s&otilde;idumeerikute kasutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in the light of experience and in view of the current state of the art it is possible to protect the connecting cables of the appliance to the impulse transmitter in order to make them inviolable by means other than a continuous plastic-coated rust-protected steel sheath with crimped ends, as presently provided for; </inglise>
<eesti> kogemuste ja praeguse tehnika taseme juures on v&otilde;imalik kaitsta seadme ja impulsisaatja vaheliste &uuml;henduskaablite rikkumatust ka muude vahenditega kui praegu etten&auml;htud teraskestaga, mis on katkematu, plastiga kaetud, roostekaitse ja valtsitud otstega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, having regard to the lifetime of the existing recording equipment, there is a need to implement this new technology in the Community construction and installation standards for electronic recording equipment; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse olemasolevate s&otilde;idumeerikute t&ouml;&ouml;iga on vaja rakendada seda uut tehnoloogiat &uuml;henduses elektrooniliste s&otilde;idumeerikute ehitus- ja paigaldusstandardites; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee for Adaptation of Regulation (EC) No 3821/85 to Technical Progress, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 kohandamist tehnika arenguga k&auml;sitleva komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Point 5 of Chapter V of Annex I to Regulation (EEC) No 3821/85 is replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3821/85 I lisa V peat&uuml;ki punkt 5 asendatakse j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> '5. </inglise>
<eesti> "5. </eesti>
<inglise> The cables connecting the recording equipment to the transmitter must be protected by a continuous plastic-coated rust-protected steel sheath with crimped ends except where an equivalent protection against manipulation is guaranteed by other means (for example by electronic monitoring such as signal encryption) capable of detecting the presence of any device, which is unnecessary for the correct operation of the recording equipment and whose purpose is to prevent the accurate operation of the recording equipment by short circuiting or interruption or by modification of the electronic data from the speed and distance sensor. </inglise>
<eesti> S&otilde;idumeerikut saatjaga &uuml;hendavad kaablid peavad olema kaitstud katkematu, plastiga kaetud, roostekaitse ja valtsitud otstega teraskestaga, v&auml;lja arvatud juhtudel, kui tagatakse samav&auml;&auml;rne manipuleerimisvastane kaitse muude vahenditega (n&auml;iteks elektrooniline seire signaali kr&uuml;pteerimise abil), mis suudavad kindlaks teha mis tahes seadme olemasolu, mis ei ole s&otilde;idumeeriku korrektseks toimimiseks vajalik ja mille eesm&auml;rk on v&auml;ltida s&otilde;idumeeriku t&auml;pset toimimist l&uuml;hise v&otilde;i katkestuse abil v&otilde;i kiiruse- ja vahemaa-anduri elektrooniliste andmete muutmise kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise> A joint, comprised of sealed connections, is deemed to be continuous within the meaning of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses loetakse &uuml;hendust katkematuks, kui see koosneb kinnistest l&uuml;litustest. </eesti>
<inglise> The aforementioned electronic monitoring may be replaced by an electronic control which ensures that the recording equipment is able to record any movement of the vehicle, independent from the signal of the speed and distance sensor. </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool nimetatud elektroonilise seire v&otilde;ib asendada elektroonilise kontrolliga, mis tagab, et s&otilde;idumeerik oleks suuteline salvestama kiiruse- ja vahemaa-anduri signaalist s&otilde;ltumatult s&otilde;iduki mis tahes liikumist." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply as from 1 January 1996. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1996. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 25 October 1995. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 25. oktoober 1995 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Neil KINNOCK Member of the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel komisjoni liige Neil KINNOCK (1) E&Uuml;T L 370, 31.12.1985, lk 8. </eesti>
 